                    float height,
                    float bearing,
                    boolean isStatic)
        Initializes a new GPSNode
        Parameters:
        id - ID of the node.
        photo - Picture that will be shown on the map.
        location - Location of the Node.
        height - Height of the object from the ground.
        bearing - Rotation of the photo. 0 Means picture is facing to East.
        isStatic - Whether the image of the node is static or not.

      • calculateTranslationVector

        private com.jme3.math.Vector3f calculateTranslationVector(float bearing,
                                                          float distance)
        Calculates translation vector with given angle and distance from node A to node B. A and B are not parameters for this function.
        Parameters:
        bearing - Bearing of the node from destination point to target point in degrees.
        distance - Distance between two nodes.
        Returns:
        Translation vector. If this vector is applied to node A, It's new position will be the same as node B's position.
